Running command: set -e
# Check /workspace exists
if [ ! -d /workspace ]; then echo "ERROR: /workspace not found" >&2; exit 1; fi
# Create tar.gz containing the 'workspace' directory (top-level folder included)
rm -f /tmp/workspace.tar.gz
tar -czf /tmp/workspace.tar.gz -C / workspace
ls -lh /tmp/workspace.tar.gz
# Upload to ownCloud WebDAV (dav/files user path)
URL="http://the-agent-company.com:8092/remote.php/dav/files/theagentcompany/Documents/workspace.tar.gz"
HTTP_CODE=$(curl -u theagentcompany:theagentcompany -T /tmp/workspace.tar.gz -s -w "%{http_code}" -o /tmp/curl_upload_resp "$URL")
echo "HTTP_CODE=$HTTP_CODE"
# If upload succeeded (201/204), verify with a HEAD request
if [ "$HTTP_CODE" = "201" ] || [ "$HTTP_CODE" = "204" ] || [ "$HTTP_CODE" = "200" ]; then
  echo "Upload appears successful. Verifying with HEAD..."
  curl -I -u theagentcompany:theagentcompany -s "$URL"
else
  echo "Upload failed with HTTP code $HTTP_CODE" >&2
  echo "Server response body:"
  sed -n '1,200p' /tmp/curl_upload_resp || true
  exit 2
fi
